    <h1>Isadora&#x2019;s Chil&#xAD;dren (2019, PG)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200904/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-04"><time>2020-09-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>In this French film, leg­endary dancer Isadora Dun­can cre­ated a farewell solo ti­tled Mother af­ter the death of her two chil­dren in April 1913.</p>
    <p>The dance fea­tures a mother cradling her child for the last time be­fore let­ting him go. A cen­tury later, four women en­counter the heartrend­ing dance. Part of Sin­gu­lar Screens for the Sin­ga­pore In­ter­na­tional Fes­ti­val of Arts cu­rated by the Asian Film Ar­chive.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Old­ham The­atre, 1 Can­ning Rise MRT: City Hall/Bras Basah</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row, 4pm, & Sept 11, 8pm AD­MIS­SION: $12 (the­atri­cal screen­ing) or $8 (video on de­mand)</p>
    <p>INFO: sifa.sg/pro­grammes/film/ isadora-s-chil­dren-sifa-v2020</p>


